rComments: he's alright...if you work really hard
Mid-term was pretty fair in my opinion. Exam was just awful, I had a 9x going in, dropped to a 78. Get the marks while you can before the exam, I'm not sure how I got a 5x% on his exam...

Has the absolute worse hand writing. Combine that with the world's most boring, put-you-to-sleep voice and you see why his class is half empty. But in terms of content he knows his stuff. Exams/midterms are hard, but he makes up for them with easy assignments.
I had better get above 80 on that course...

For you first year commerce students - I definitely recommend you take Bertrand mgt223 course if he teaches this summer. Trust me!  His lectures were excellent. While slides were abundant, they were helpful. Don't forget, he is not easy neither is the course, but if you the assigned readings and questions, you'll do fine. One great summer indeed!!!

bertrand is a machine...doesnt use much notes to lecture and recites everything almost word for word from text. i wish lectures were a little more fun, but they are still worth attending since he teaches everythign you need to know. his watch is hot.
decent prof - the course matter itself is kinda gay, but strictly speaking, this guy knows his sh!t.  responds to student queries via email and always helpful in person.

his voice definitely puts you to sleep. its not just him the course is quite monotonous anyways. all in all a good guy, no comment on the marking scheme of things. one good thing, he will answer almost any question you throw at him related to the business world.
